But why would a corporate magnate borrow
from Kim Myeong-gil? I don't get that?

269
00:19:12.151 --> 00:19:14.111
Well. Myeong-gil probably tricked them.

270
00:19:15.612 --> 00:19:17.156
- Let's find out.
- Mm.

271
00:19:18.907 --> 00:19:19.907
[sighs]

272
00:19:20.367 --> 00:19:22.161
Finally avenging our boys.

273
00:19:23.912 --> 00:19:24.912
Let's end this.

274
00:19:25.664 --> 00:19:27.166
Mr. Choi gave us his approval.

275
00:19:27.833 --> 00:19:29.209
[dramatic music playing]

276
00:19:30.002 --> 00:19:31.002
Mm.

277
00:19:31.670 --> 00:19:36.300
Back in the day. President Choi
had fiveÂ knifers working for him.

278
00:19:36.383 --> 00:19:39.928
During that time.
he would lend money to corporations.

279
00:19:40.012 --> 00:19:42.431
so he often had
10 billion won or more uncollected.

280
00:19:42.514 --> 00:19:44.558
But places like construction companies

281
00:19:45.225 --> 00:19:47.936
would always have gangs
that would be looking out for them.

282
00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:49.646
That's when these guys would go.

283
00:19:49.730 --> 00:19:53.317
They would go out
and obliterate an entire gang in a day.

284
00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:57.654
Back then. even the big gangs were
terrified of President Choi's knifers.

285
00:19:59.656 --> 00:20:02.409
When I finally got Choi out of the way.

286
00:20:03.577 --> 00:20:05.913
the first thing Beom and I did
was get rid of the knifers.

287
00:20:05.996 --> 00:20:08.248
And do you have an idea
of why we did that?

288
00:20:09.583 --> 00:20:10.583
Uh. no.

289
00:20:11.835 --> 00:20:14.838
Because I was scared as fuck too.
you know?

290
00:20:14.922 --> 00:20:16.965
[all laughing]

291
00:20:17.049 --> 00:20:18.800
You and In-beom took them out alone?

292
00:20:18.884 --> 00:20:23.347
We sent two gangs. one from Sindang-dong
and one from Yeongdeungpo. as a unit.

293
00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:26.266
We were able to do it
because they weren't together at the time.

294
00:20:26.350 --> 00:20:28.602
Otherwise. it would have been impossible.

295
00:20:28.685 --> 00:20:30.520
Wow. That's amazing. sir.

296
00:20:30.604 --> 00:20:31.855
But in the end.

297
00:20:33.023 --> 00:20:35.901
I couldn't get rid of
the two most important ones.

298
00:20:36.985 --> 00:20:40.113
Lee Du-yeong and Hwang Yang-jung.

299
00:20:40.697 --> 00:20:43.742
President Choi's left and right-hand men.

300
00:20:45.285 --> 00:20:50.207
Back when I was President Choi's lackey.
I once had a run-in with Lee Du-yeong.

301
00:20:50.290 --> 00:20:51.290
He's handsome.

302
00:20:53.001 --> 00:20:55.712
This one time.
a gang leader was stuck in traffic.

303
00:20:55.796 --> 00:20:58.090
so he was having a smoke
with his window rolled down.

304
00:20:58.173 --> 00:21:00.968
He heard a motorcycle approaching.
so he turned his head.

305
00:21:01.051 --> 00:21:05.264
And Lee Du-yeong carved his face like this
with a sashimi knife.

306
00:21:05.347 --> 00:21:07.474
Fuck. his mouth was bleeding.
flapping in the wind.

307
00:21:07.557 --> 00:21:09.101
Shit. that's amazing.

308
00:21:11.061 --> 00:21:12.141
Who's Hwang Yang-jung. sir?

309
00:21:12.187 --> 00:21:14.231
Well. they say

310
00:21:15.774 --> 00:21:18.819
that he made cripples
out of 20 gang members

311
00:21:18.902 --> 00:21:20.821
by severing their Achilles tendons solo.

312
00:21:20.904 --> 00:21:24.950
I've also heard he uses two knives at once
and can stab a hundred times in a minute.

313
00:21:26.034 --> 00:21:27.327
Crazy shit.

314
00:21:29.288 --> 00:21:30.539
[chuckles]

315
00:21:31.707 --> 00:21:33.625
Did you say that three kids showed up?

316
00:21:33.709 --> 00:21:36.545
Yes. A girl showed up about halfway.

317
00:21:37.045 --> 00:21:40.215
And I think she's somehow connected
to that bookstore I mentioned to you.

318
00:21:40.799 --> 00:21:41.799
[chuckles]

319
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:45.637
It would make sense
if Choi owns the bookstore.

320
00:21:45.721 --> 00:21:49.850
That senile fuck must have crawled out
of the shadows to save his kids.

321
00:21:49.933 --> 00:21:51.101
[laughing]

322
00:21:52.269 --> 00:21:54.104
Do you know
how much money President Choi has?

323
00:21:55.772 --> 00:21:59.776
I'd guess. in cash. about 50 billion.

324
00:21:59.860 --> 00:22:03.113
[gasps] That could fully cover the money
we're short on. sir.

325
00:22:03.196 --> 00:22:04.948
[laughing]

326
00:22:05.032 --> 00:22:08.744
Well. I guess
someone up there's looking out for us.

327
00:22:08.827 --> 00:22:10.704
[all laugh]

328
00:22:11.455 --> 00:22:13.957
Jang-do and Beom.
I want you to stake out the place

329
00:22:14.041 --> 00:22:15.250
